snippet.textDisplay:
Amazing rendition of a national classic. Loving the symphony and the collection of our great voices.

Seeing Amjad Sabri Sahib brought tears to my eyes. Would have loved to see Sajjad Ali and Shehzad Roy also included.

I would suggest for patriotic songs have the ambiance in hues of white and green if possible.

Lastly for all the people trashing in the comments I would suggest you to read history from a neutral perspective. 

I am not doubting the sacrifices made for Pakistan for even a second but the partition was a bloody affair. There was alot killing of Hindu, Muslim, Sikh, Christian and other religious sects. Every human life matters. Every single freaking life matter.

Don't feed the trolls.

snippet.textDisplay: It makes me feel proud that in this era of utter despair and ordeal we Pakistanis repeatedly come up with some special moments,whether it be such a piece of artistic brilliance or famous Lord's celebrations which helps unite us all as a nation.Coke studio has always entertained us and maintained high standards throughout but this is something different. The lyrics,voices of the legends and music penetrate one's soul and come out as tears through the eyes.Independence day coming up and emotions at their peak...Hats off to our brave soldiers.We will never forget your sacrifices.Pakistan Paaindabad!!!
